#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.12, pts-cs-bu-pc3.1, pts-vp-en.2.186, ms2V_111
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharanti;"
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six were engaged in malicious talebearing between monks who were arguing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.3"
msgid "imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyanti, imassa bhedāya; amussa sutvā imassa akkhāyanti, amussa bhedāya."
msgstr "After hearing something on one side they reported it to the other side, and vice versa, in order to create division between them."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.4"
msgid "Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr "In this way new quarrels were created and existing quarrels became worse."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.5"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.6"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.7"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharissanti, imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyissanti, imassa bhedāya;"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six engage in malicious talebearing between monks who are arguing?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.8"
msgid "amussa sutvā imassa akkhāyissanti, amussa bhedāya."
msgstr "How can they report to one side what they have heard on the other side, and vice versa, in order to create division,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.9"
msgid "Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr "and in this way create new quarrels and make existing quarrels worse?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_112
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.10"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.11"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharatha, imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyatha, imassa bhedāya, amussa sutvā imassa akkhāyatha, amussa bhedāya?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.12"
msgid "Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattantī”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.13"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.14"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.15"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharissatha."
msgstr "“… Foolish men, how can you engage in malicious talebearing between monks who are arguing?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.16"
msgid "Imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyissatha, imassa bhedāya. Amussa sutvā imassa akkhāyissatha, amussa bhedāya."
msgstr "How can you report to one side what you have heard on the other side, and vice versa, in order to create division,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.17"
msgid "Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr "and in this way create new quarrels and make existing quarrels worse?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya."
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.19"
msgid "Pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya … pe …"
msgstr "or increase the confidence of those who have it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.20"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.20a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

# NOTE: This is translated somewhat freely in accordance with the explanation below and in the commentary. According to [](MS.2.144) (see below) the offense is only incurred when a monk brings the words of another monk to the attention of yet another monk, and thus the translation “between monks.” [](Sp.4.740.20) supports the plural rendering “monks”: “malicious talebearing of monks,” _bhikkhūnaṃ pesuññe_.
#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_113
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:1.21"
msgid "“Bhikkhupesuññe pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk engages in malicious talebearing between monks, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

